Transcription.Text: My father hung upon every word, but could get nothing from him. When he saw Trelawny's printed letter, Lord Sidney wrote to Douglas Kinnaird saying that it was incorrect throughout. His only reference to Trelawny by name in the course of several communications to Hobhouse and Kinnaird about Byron's affairs is satirical:
